{{Infobox organisation |name = South Pacific Regional Fisheries Management Organisation |former name = |image = SPRFMO.png |image_size = |alt = |caption = Logo of the South Pacific Regional Fisheries Management Organisation |map = |map_size = |map_caption = |abbreviation = SPRFMO |motto = |formation = {{Start date and age|2012|08|24|df=yes|p=y}} |type = [[International organization]] |status = |purpose = [[Fisheries]] |headquarters = [[Wellington]], [[New Zealand]] |membership = 15 members |coords = {{coord|41.2858901|S|174.7726154|E|display=inline,title}} |area_served = South Pacific |founder = |leader_title = Executive Secretary |leader_name = Dr Sebastian Rodriguez |website = {{URL|https://www.sprfmo.int}} }}
The '''South Pacific Regional Fisheries Management Organisation''' (SPRFMO) is an [[intergovernmental organization]] created by [[international treaty]], the ''Convention on the Conservation and Management of High Seas Fishery Resources in the South Pacific Ocean'' signed in [[Auckland]] on {{dts|14 November 2009}}.<ref name="treaty">[http://www.austlii.edu.au/au/other/dfat/treaties/ATS/2012/28.html "Convention on the Conservation and Management of High Seas Fishery Resources in the South Pacific Ocean (Auckland, 14 November 2009) – ATS 28 of 2012”]. Australasian Legal Information Institute, Australian Treaties Library. Retrieved on 18 April 2017.</ref>
The intent of the signatories was to commit "to ensuring the long-term conservation and sustainable use of fishery resources in the South Pacific Ocean and in so doing safeguarding the marine ecosystems in which the resources occur."<ref name="treaty" />
==Secretariat== The secretariat of SPRFMO is based in [[Wellington]], [[New Zealand]]. Currently the Executive Secretary is Dr Sebastian Rodriguez <ref>{{cite web|title=South Pacific Regional Management Organisation|url=https://www.sprfmo.int/new-meetingpage-Contacts/|website=www.sprfmo.int|accessdate=1 July 2017}}</ref>
